20/04/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Bulgarian Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg and his Macedonian counterpart, Branko Crvenkovski, agreed Friday (18 April) that the level of trade between the two countries is low, and that their governments should do their best to remove all administrative obstacles and boost economic co-operation.
Saxe-Coburg, on his first visit ever to Macedonia, held talks with representatives of the opposition VMRO-DPMNE.
He also met with the leaders of all Albanian parties in the country.
During the three day visit, Saxe-Coburg will also meet with President Boris Trajkovski and other officials.(Sega - 19/04/03;
MIA, Makfax, A1 TV, BTA - 18/04/03)
